<!--donate-->
<br> 
    <section id="donate" class="donate">
        <br>
        <h1>Why Donate Blood?</h1>

        <br>
        <br>
        <p>Blood donation is not just an act of kindness; it is a life-saving service. Here’s why you should donate:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>It helps save lives and improve community health.</li>
            <li>Regular donations keep blood banks stocked and ready for emergencies.</li>
            <li>Donors often enjoy health benefits such as reduced risk of heart diseases.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
<br>

<!--Donation process-->
<br>
<section class="donation-process">
    <h1>Donation Process</h1>
    <p>Your generous contribution can make a significant impact and help save lives in need.</p>
    <div class="process-container">
      <div class="process-step">
        <img src="11.jfif" alt="Eligibility Check">
        <h2>Eligibility Check</h2>
        <p>Ensure you meet the requirements for blood donation, including being in good health, meeting age and weight criteria, and not having certain medical conditions or engaging in high-risk behaviors.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <img src="1.pgn.jfif" alt="Register and Screen">
        <h2>Register and Screen</h2>
        <p>Sign up as a donor and go through a screening process, which includes a confidential interview to assess your health, travel history, and potential risk factors for transmitting infections.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <img src="download.jfif" alt="Donate Blood">
        <h2>Donate Blood</h2>
        <p>Undergo the blood donation process, where a healthcare professional will collect a pint of blood through a sterile needle inserted into your vein.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="process-step">
        <img src="4.jfif" alt="Post-Donation Care">
        <h2>Post-Donation Care</h2>
        <p>After donation, a bandage will be applied to your arm. Rest and refreshments are provided to help replenish lost fluids and nutrients.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
